1
00:00:01,092 --> 00:00:03,092
Dr. Khalifa:
I seek refuge in God from Satan the rejected (أعوذ بِٱللَّهِ مِنَ ٱلشَّيْطَـٰنِ ٱلرَّجِيمِ) [A'oodhu billahi min ash-shaytan ir-rajeem]

2
00:00:03,092 --> 00:00:05,373
We seek refuge in God from Satan.

3
00:00:07,006 --> 00:00:08,643
Bism Allah Arrahman Arraheem

4
00:00:09,006 --> 00:00:11,550
In the name of God, Most Gracious, Most Merciful

5
00:00:12,267 --> 00:00:15,558
Tonight, we're starting at Sura 54,

6
00:00:17,251 --> 00:00:18,646
55, excuse me.

7
00:00:19,735 --> 00:00:22,279
And our teacher tonight will be Laurie, right?

8
00:00:23,088 --> 00:00:25,967
But before we start, I want to make some corrections.

9
00:00:26,693 --> 00:00:29,655
In my Khutba today, I make some boo-boos
sometimes.

10
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:35,138
Sometimes I say things that appear to be not
very tactful.

11
00:00:35,683 --> 00:00:41,421
For example, we have here a great team of
cake-bringers or cake-makers.

12
00:00:41,904 --> 00:00:48,272
And when I asked, then Rahima was... it was Rahima's turn, Laurie's
turn, I said "the best."

13
00:00:48,635 --> 00:00:53,519
So, this... they're all, they're all great makers of cakes, bringers
of cakes.

14
00:00:53,761 --> 00:01:00,516
And this appears not to be tactful, but I
have to explain to you that each believer is the best.

15
00:01:00,516 --> 00:01:05,461
So, when I, when I say "the best," I'm referring to every
single one of them.

16
00:01:06,511 --> 00:01:08,449
Because we're all...

17
00:01:08,765 --> 00:01:10,476
I hope I don't make it worse.

18
00:01:11,664 --> 00:01:18,130
No, honest, I, because you people are so special
that every one of you is the best.

19
00:01:18,130 --> 00:01:29,508
And when I say that, I just want to pay you the highest possible compliment without infringing on the others' properties.

20
00:01:30,362 --> 00:01:33,466
But they all are the best, each one of them.

21
00:01:39,151 --> 00:01:40,406
Every single...

22
00:01:42,704 --> 00:01:46,507
Did I describe your cake as the best when
you brought it in?

23
00:01:49,107 --> 00:01:50,669
Now how do I get out of this one?

24
00:01:51,456 --> 00:01:52,456
Help!

25
00:01:54,270 --> 00:01:57,978
I think I'll get out by saying "okay, take it
over, Laurie."

26
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,788
Laurie:
I seek refuge in God from Satan the rejected (أعوذ بِٱللَّهِ مِنَ ٱلشَّيْطَـٰنِ ٱلرَّجِيمِ) [A'oodhu billahi min ash-shaytan ir-rajeem]

27
00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:11,956
I take refuge in God from Satan the rejected.

28
00:02:12,682 --> 00:02:15,000
In the name of God, Most Gracious, Most Merciful

29
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:20,512
[55:1]  GOD, Most Gracious.
[55:2]  The One who teaches the Quran.

30
00:02:21,056 --> 00:02:23,298
[55:3]  The One who created the human beings.

31
00:02:23,661 --> 00:02:26,810
[55:4]  The One who taught him how to distinguish right from wrong.

32
00:02:27,838 --> 00:02:30,745
[55:5]  The sun and the moon created his timing devices

33
00:02:31,592 --> 00:02:33,592
[55:6]  The stars and the trees prostrate.

34
00:02:34,439 --> 00:02:37,044
[55:7]  He raised the heaven and established the balance.

35
00:02:37,588 --> 00:02:39,588
[55:8]  You shall not transgress when you weigh.

36
00:02:40,132 --> 00:02:43,583
[55:9]  You shall be equitable when you weigh; do not cheat when you trade.

37
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,430
[55:10]  He made the earth for all the people.

38
00:02:47,095 --> 00:02:49,760
[55:11]  With fruits, and palms sheath.

39
00:02:50,002 --> 00:02:52,002
[55:12]  With food grains and flowers.

40
00:02:52,728 --> 00:02:55,575
[55:13]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

41
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:59,027
[55:14]  He created the human from clay, like the potter's.

42
00:02:59,027 --> 00:03:01,995
[55:15]  And created the jinns from blazing fire.

43
00:03:02,539 --> 00:03:04,962
[55:16]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

44
00:03:05,748 --> 00:03:08,111
[55:17]  Lord of the two easts and the two wests.

45
00:03:08,595 --> 00:03:11,381
[55:18]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

46
00:03:12,711 --> 00:03:15,497
[55:19]  He separates the fresh water from the salt water.

47
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:18,586
[55:20]  Between them is a barrier they cannot surmount.

48
00:03:19,070 --> 00:03:21,977
[55:21]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

49
00:03:22,461 --> 00:03:25,791
[55:22]  From the two seas you extract pearls and coral.

50
00:03:26,396 --> 00:03:28,819
[55:23]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

51
00:03:30,331 --> 00:03:33,299
[55:24]  He controls the ships that roam the sea like flags.

52
00:03:33,662 --> 00:03:36,206
[55:25]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

53
00:03:37,416 --> 00:03:39,235
[55:26]  Everyone on earth will perish.

54
00:03:39,477 --> 00:03:44,440
[55:27]  But the presence of your Lord will continue. He is the Possessor of Majesty and Honor.

55
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,605
[55:28]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

56
00:03:48,028 --> 00:03:53,838
[55:29]  Everyone in the heavens and the earth implores Him. Every day He is in full control.

57
00:03:54,201 --> 00:03:57,048
[55:30]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

58
00:03:57,713 --> 00:04:01,588
[55:31]  We will deal with both of you, the two entities, humans and jinns.

59
00:04:01,830 --> 00:04:04,858
[55:32]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

60
00:04:05,281 --> 00:04:14,659
[55:33]  O you jinns and humans, if you can penetrate the outer limits of the heavens and the earth, then penetrate. You can only penetrate when given authority.

61
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,786
[55:34]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

62
00:04:18,330 --> 00:04:23,474
[55:35]  You will be bombarded with masses of fire and molten metal, and you can never succeed.

63
00:04:24,018 --> 00:04:26,683
[55:36]  Which of your Lord's marvels can you two deny?

64
00:04:27,832 --> 00:04:29,590
Dr. Khalifa: Are you checking the tape, David?

65
00:04:29,590 --> 00:04:31,095
This is why we should be checking them.

66
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:33,216
Do the same thing over there.

67
00:04:33,579 --> 00:04:35,216
(unintelligible) has grown up enough now.

68
00:04:43,985 --> 00:04:45,380
Take good care of him.

69
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:54,395
Laurie: This chapter is very special to me, because
I have this weakness that I'm very impatient

70
00:04:54,395 --> 00:04:57,752
with knowledge, and if I don't know something,
I can't grasp it.

71
00:04:58,025 --> 00:05:02,934
And it always caused me trouble in school,
because if I didn't understand it, I couldn't do anything about it.

72
00:05:02,934 --> 00:05:09,705
And I became Muslim, and I read the Quran, and I found out that I had to submit, even though I didn't understand something.

73
00:05:09,984 --> 00:05:13,464
It was really a test for me, because I just
wanted to know.

74
00:05:13,464 --> 00:05:18,939
And I never understood the jinns. I wish like... And I read it and I knew that they...

75
00:05:18,939 --> 00:05:19,911
Thank you.

76
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:27,535
And I knew because it was in the Quran. I had to believe it, but I didn't know what they were, and nobody could explain it to me.

77
00:05:27,535 --> 00:05:32,327
You know, and I got really wild explanations of what
the jinns were.

78
00:05:32,610 --> 00:05:37,443
And it always troubled me, but I just forced
myself to submit.

79
00:05:37,746 --> 00:05:42,753
And in
the second chapter of the Quran, where it says that

80
00:05:42,753 --> 00:05:46,993
"the believers are those who believe
in the unseen." And this was part of the unseen.

81
00:05:47,598 --> 00:05:52,743
And I knew that, IN SHAA ALLAH, over time, that
God would explain it to me.

82
00:05:53,832 --> 00:05:58,916
And one of the blessings of being in this
mosque is having things explained to us.

83
00:05:59,158 --> 00:06:07,629
And as Rashad said in the Khutba today, it's a mercy from God that He sends a messenger from among us to explain to us.

84
00:06:08,029 --> 00:06:11,944
The knowledge is here in the Quran, and all
of us have read the Quran.

85
00:06:12,246 --> 00:06:15,492
You know, I read it once a month, from front
to back.

86
00:06:15,492 --> 00:06:17,367
And every time there's something new.

87
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:22,356
And we get what we need at the time we need
it.

88
00:06:22,901 --> 00:06:27,015
And we in this mosque are just developing
so far. It's just amazing.

89
00:06:27,259 --> 00:06:32,975
You know, Rashad and Lisa and Hasan went
to Canada, and there were the people believed they way we do.

90
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:39,209
They're still way behind us in the knowledge, because we're here every Friday night, learning and studying.

91
00:06:39,209 --> 00:06:42,237
We have the input of all these believers here.

92
00:06:42,237 --> 00:06:47,261
And we have a messenger that is given the
knowledge that is passed on to us.

93
00:06:47,926 --> 00:06:50,773
And we're responsible for the information
in the Quran.

94
00:06:51,234 --> 00:06:57,417
And, you know, the verse in the Quran that
was admonishing the (unintelligible), saying that

95
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:02,209
they were believers when they weren't really.
They were just submitters, and that's the first step.

96
00:07:02,209 --> 00:07:05,729
But only the believers can attain Paradise.

97
00:07:05,729 --> 00:07:11,691
So, if we don't have absolute certainty, we
can't ever grow and develop to our fullest extent.

98
00:07:11,977 --> 00:07:15,000
And that's where the increased knowledge is
that should bless me.

99
00:07:16,518 --> 00:07:19,901
And I read, you know, I've read this verse
so many times, and the first time I read it,

100
00:07:19,901 --> 00:07:23,792
you too, the humans and the jinns, you know,
I just didn't understand what it meant.

101
00:07:23,792 --> 00:07:30,000
I didn't understand what the jinns were, what
their role was, what they had to do with me or with us.

102
00:07:30,786 --> 00:07:37,926
It was just a mystery. And I just, you know, like I said, I had to
force myself not to question it, not to be hung up about it.

103
00:07:37,926 --> 00:07:43,917
When we had that discussion about jinns in the Quranic studies, I just kept my mouth shut, you know, very different things.

104
00:07:44,548 --> 00:07:52,255
But now, just in this last year, we found
out what this is, and so this chapter has a totally different meaning.

105
00:07:52,665 --> 00:07:56,074
And for the first time, I understand what
it means.

106
00:07:56,558 --> 00:08:02,098
And we know now that the jinns are, you know,
they have the same requirements.

107
00:08:02,098 --> 00:08:05,947
There's other verses in the Quran that they
have the same requirements that we do.

108
00:08:05,947 --> 00:08:10,791
Some of them believed in Jesus, and they believed
in other things, and then they heard the Quran,

109
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:16,299
and they believed, and, you know, they have
the same requirements that we do.

110
00:08:16,592 --> 00:08:19,228
And they also have the same rewards that we
do.

111
00:08:19,773 --> 00:08:25,254
You know, there are entities that we can't see. You know, we don't know. They can see us, but we can't see them.

112
00:08:25,585 --> 00:08:29,162
And yet, the Heaven that's described here
in later verses is for them, too.

113
00:08:29,162 --> 00:08:34,790
They have their own, but it's the same set-up as ours. It's exactly the same for them.

114
00:08:35,758 --> 00:08:41,024
Like, you know, these creatures that are so
important in this scripture that we don't know anything about.

115
00:08:41,637 --> 00:08:48,339
And now we know that the jinns were those
that, before creation, sided with Satan and

116
00:08:48,339 --> 00:08:56,814
took a stand against God and believed that Satan could be a god besides God, that God could have partners, which is the ultimate blasphemy.

117
00:08:57,360 --> 00:09:02,815
And they were banished, and they have a
chance to redeem themselves as well.

118
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:08,703
And our job is to, you know, and I used to
read about Satan and his troops

119
00:09:08,703 --> 00:09:13,722
and generations of jinns and humans, that I didn't know, how
do they, how do they come to be generations?

120
00:09:13,722 --> 00:09:18,774
How do they multiply? How do they, you know, what do they do to
reproduce themselves?

121
00:09:19,217 --> 00:09:25,266
Now we know that a jinn is assigned to
each one of us, and so their reproduction is,

122
00:09:25,266 --> 00:09:31,293
it coincides with our reproduction, that
each one of us is given a companion at

123
00:09:31,293 --> 00:09:37,541
the time of our entry into this world, and we're
in the same boat. We both sinned.

124
00:09:37,541 --> 00:09:40,509
We both came to this earth with original sin.

125
00:09:40,509 --> 00:09:47,287
We both took a stand against God, the jinns
more forcefully than we did, but we took the same stand

126
00:09:47,287 --> 00:09:50,497
as not being for God, because there's
only two ways.

127
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:55,159
Either you're for or you're against, and we
were wishy-washy, but basically we were against God.

128
00:09:55,159 --> 00:09:58,002
We've both been given the chance to redeem ourselves.

129
00:09:59,332 --> 00:10:07,682
Thing is, the jinns took the definite stand. So, they're going to try to convert us to Satan's way of thinking and to the original sin that we committed.

130
00:10:08,070 --> 00:10:10,613
So, we have to convert them.

131
00:10:11,036 --> 00:10:18,190
So from the time of birth, we're in this constant
struggle with our jinn companion to convert them to righteousness

132
00:10:18,190 --> 00:10:21,525
and to protect ourselves
from falling into the path of the jinn.

133
00:10:21,887 --> 00:10:27,037
And It's a struggle. It's a struggle every day of our lives, and
it just goes on and on.

134
00:10:27,677 --> 00:10:34,688
And the blessing about knowing who your enemy
is, is knowing what they are, what their goal is,

135
00:10:34,688 --> 00:10:37,779
what their tactics are, so you can learn
how to defend yourself.

136
00:10:37,779 --> 00:10:41,066
And that's what the Quran is, and that's where
these blessings come from.

137
00:10:42,043 --> 00:10:43,426
So, we know that.

138
00:10:43,426 --> 00:10:48,851
And to me, the greatest blessing of all is
knowing that we do have original sin and we're bad.

139
00:10:48,851 --> 00:10:52,786
You know, we were born bad, because we took the stand
against God.

140
00:10:52,786 --> 00:10:55,633
So now that we know that, we know what we
have to do.

141
00:10:55,935 --> 00:11:02,773
We have to, just every day of our lives, try
to redeem ourselves from that sin.

142
00:11:03,741 --> 00:11:09,611
And the Quran is very specific about giving
us the way to do it, and we know now,

143
00:11:09,611 --> 00:11:15,360
we've heard it several times in Khutbas, that we have
to ask ourselves every day "who is my god this week?"

144
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:22,091
Ok. Because that's our only goal in life, is to
redeem ourselves. Nothing else has any importance whatsoever.

145
00:11:22,627 --> 00:11:28,945
And we have to do certain things. We have to support ourselves. We have to take care of ourselves. But

146
00:11:28,945 --> 00:11:36,425
with the goal in mind that this is to do righteousness, you know, we can't be a burden to society, we can't steal, so we have to work and support ourselves.

147
00:11:36,425 --> 00:11:42,537
So, it's all in tune with the same thing, which
is purifying ourselves, and growing and developing our souls.

148
00:11:43,804 --> 00:11:48,910
So as soon as you take that stand, then the
jinns are going to try to,

149
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:52,556
your companion and others are going to try and make you stray
away from that path.

150
00:11:53,161 --> 00:12:00,475
And the greater the stand you take, the greater the enticements are going to be, and you just have to be prepared.

151
00:12:00,475 --> 00:12:03,489
And I've talked to several people who've said
that they've encountered the same thing I

152
00:12:03,489 --> 00:12:09,803
did when I made the stand, that I was going
to really try and devote more of my thoughts

153
00:12:09,803 --> 00:12:13,774
to God because I wasn't doing enough, and
I knew it, that they just took over,

154
00:12:13,774 --> 00:12:19,696
and they didn't want me to, even the little that I
was doing was in danger of not being done at all.

155
00:12:19,696 --> 00:12:21,454
It's just a constant struggle.

156
00:12:21,817 --> 00:12:30,000
And so I know this now, and I know that I
have to just be on the alert at all times for, for this. And we know that

157
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:35,870
most of it is sneaky whispering.
And there's even a Sura where, you know, this is

158
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:42,236
devoted to this, that Satan whispers to us, I mean, little
things that don't seem so bad.

159
00:12:42,236 --> 00:12:46,715
You know, we've talked about this before. "Oh, you can
wait until the game is over before you pray" or

160
00:12:46,715 --> 00:12:49,804
you know "I'll pray later," and then something happens
and you don't pray.

161
00:12:50,178 --> 00:12:54,604
And that time can never be regained. Once you miss the Prayer, you can't make it up. That time is...

162
00:12:55,269 --> 00:12:58,962
The inhabitants of Hell are the farthest from
God on the Day of Judgment.

163
00:12:59,264 --> 00:13:04,651
Knowing that Heaven is close to God, they
will leave Hell and sneak into the area closer to God,

164
00:13:04,651 --> 00:13:08,284
but because they are not sufficiently
prepared to come close to God,

165
00:13:08,284 --> 00:13:13,671
they will suffer terribly in the presence of God and will flee
back to Hell and so on forever.

166
00:13:13,671 --> 00:13:17,001
Here's this vicious circle that they're
in.

167
00:13:18,573 --> 00:13:20,392
A man: It's just like the Jehovah's Witnesses now.

168
00:13:20,392 --> 00:13:27,301
They don't believe in Hell, but they
believe 144,000 go to Heaven and the remainder

169
00:13:27,301 --> 00:13:33,504
of their chosen people or whatever go to Paradise. But they still deny Hell.

170
00:13:34,066 --> 00:13:40,850
They say "there's no burning Hell. There's no
none of this. You just no longer exist,"

171
00:13:40,850 --> 00:13:48,777
which is a lie of... outright lying itself, because
nothing that exists can be destroyed.

172
00:13:49,326 --> 00:13:56,406
You know, like matter can't be created or
destroyed, ever destroyed. It just recycles.

173
00:13:56,967 --> 00:14:02,095
In the real world that we're in. No, in the other
world, this is not the real world, but in the world we're in now.

174
00:14:02,410 --> 00:14:10,798
So, they don't believe in Hell, because if
you tell them anything contrary to anything pleasant after death,

175
00:14:10,798 --> 00:14:14,536
they say "well, we just
don't exist anymore."

176
00:14:14,536 --> 00:14:17,746
"Well, we never get punished for what we do
wrong."

177
00:14:18,048 --> 00:14:20,713
"And that's our punishment, not existing."

178
00:14:21,015 --> 00:14:24,529
"Well, we can get a reward. If we're real good,
we get this reward."

179
00:14:24,529 --> 00:14:27,966
"But if we're real bad, we just don't exist
anymore."

180
00:14:27,966 --> 00:14:30,000
"Just have a reward and no punishment."

181
00:14:30,477 --> 00:14:31,968
Dr. Khalifa: They wish, they wish this.

182
00:14:31,968 --> 00:14:33,593
A man: That's what I'm saying. This, this is...
A woman: Thank you.

183
00:14:33,593 --> 00:14:34,501
Dr. Khalifa: Quran...

184
00:14:34,501 --> 00:14:37,106
A man: This is what I thought about it.
Dr. Khalifa: The Quran says 'they will wish that they..."

185
00:14:37,106 --> 00:14:40,074
A man: Yeah. "This is the Hell they used to deny."
Dr. Khalifa: Yes.

186
00:14:40,074 --> 00:14:43,223
A man: They deny Hell.
Dr. Khalifa: Exactly.

187
00:14:43,669 --> 00:14:47,229
Dr. Khalifa: I just wanna add here something that we
should all know.

188
00:14:50,616 --> 00:14:54,486
I know Laurie knows that but she just didn't mention it yet.

189
00:14:55,025 --> 00:14:56,330
It has to do with the looks.

190
00:14:56,814 --> 00:15:00,351
See, verse 40 says, (unintelligible), number 39.

191
00:15:04,947 --> 00:15:06,947
Where's the...

192
00:15:07,612 --> 00:15:09,914
Well, not they ask...Oh, 39, yeah.

193
00:15:10,458 --> 00:15:14,333
"The humans and the jinn will not be asked
about their sins."

194
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:21,497
Nobody will need to ask anybody about anything,
because the believers develop their souls,

195
